  <data name="FullDescription" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>An element or flow that declares an encryption algorithm should use a modern, authenticated cipher. Non-authenticated or legacy ciphers (for example secretbox / XSalsa20-Poly1305, AES-CBC without a MAC, 3DES, or RC4) are weaker and, for some organizations, are not compliant (non-FIPS / non-NIST).

This rule is violated for any element or flow whose Algorithm (or Cipher) property names a cipher that is not one of the approved authenticated ciphers: AES-GCM, AES-CBC with HMAC, or ChaCha20-Poly1305. It does not fire when no algorithm is declared.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="HelpText" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Set the element's Algorithm (or Cipher) property to an approved authenticated cipher: AES-GCM, AES-CBC+HMAC, or ChaCha20-Poly1305. For the KEK/DEK path, migrate secretbox (XSalsa20-Poly1305) to AES-GCM.

If the value is a placeholder rather than a real cipher, set it to None (or remove the property) so the rule does not apply.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="MessageText" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>The {0} declares the encryption algorithm '{1}', which is not an approved authenticated cipher. Migrate it to AES-GCM, AES-CBC with HMAC, or ChaCha20-Poly1305.</value>
